        <p>Thomaston Mills attributed its lower sales and earnings in the latest fiscal year to slower economic conditions, escalating raw material prices and lower than normal capacity use. The company said expenditures for new plant and equipment amounted to $ 19.6 million in the latest fiscal year, with investments were made in the areas of spinning, weaving, automated sewing, a chemical recover system and an expansion of its Pike denim facility. Thomaston said it has significantly increased capacity, and said continued investment in state-of-the-art production facilities should provide higher quality products at lower cost.</p>
